1721 Project is the joint creation of sisters Telalit Charsky (cello, voice) and Nuphar Fey (piano, composition). The Current show of the 1721 Project is The Cyclic Night - a tantalizing fusion of old and new music including Tango Nuevo, Bach and other Baroque composers, and original music. 
Cyclic Night has two versions: one is classical, with a new album coming out in April 2016 under the Dutch record label Silvox Studios; the second is electronic, with the theme of short night stories which are recorded and blended in the music.
For more information about the Cyclic Night and the activities of the 1721 Project, visit www.1721project.com 
Subscribe to the project on YouTube here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6jXTaHDjyTg

Founded in June 2006, 1724 Records, which is located in Beijing, is a mini label focusing on spreading indie music.

The name 1724 roots in that truth: the feeling and inspiration in youth will affect the trajectory of your life. 1724 Records believes that music has the power to rebuild the shape of our soul. Based on this concept they have issued albums and eps for musicians such as 48V, Thumb Girls, oNEwAY, kayak, pentatonic, punkwei, YiyuanLiang and Summer Fades Away.

Now 1724 Records is concentrating on Post-rock and Folk music, including electronic, experimental, ambient and some other types. They are trying to bloom indie music and hope that more and more people can touch the feeling of youth through their music.


As a branch of the net media IndieChina(http://www.indiechina.com/), 1724 records is also engaged in artist management. Till now they have organized numbers of live shows and music festivals for their musicians .(edited by Gilbertea)
